                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "I am sorry but I cannot agree with this at all. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "DPI is a grapical device parameter with one specific purpose: match pixel and physical resolution of the deivce so that *all* output may be scaled to make it readable regardless of physical pixel density. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Given that pixel density of the modern displays tends to increase the approach you suggesting is a dead end, all output must be scaled, there may be no pixel-sizing at all - it is as grave a mistake as a hardcoding. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "If someone has been sufficiently unwise to consider these complaints as bugs and 'fix' them, it should be undone with utmost expedience. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Incidentally when you say 'decoupled' do you mean that you introduced a configuration option to apply a global non-1 zoom factor to all HTML documents? ", 
